    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce 'Grow Your Own' Laws for Legal Medical Cannabis Patients",
        "additional_details": "We believe patients prescribed by a medical specialist should be allowed to maintain 3-6 flowering plants (with extra considerations for starting new seedlings.) A registration database could be maintained for grow your own patients\r\n \r\nIt has been estimated that there are around 25-30,000 legal medical cannabis patients across the UK. Patients can face severe financial difficulty affording their prescription.\r\n \r\n\"Grow Your Own\" is available to cannabis patients in many other countries.\r\n",
        "background": "Allow patients that are prescribed cannabis to grow their own cannabis at home with a restriction of 6 plants per household. This is to assist people with financial difficulty who may not be able to afford a private prescription.",
